aggregate measure takes into account PISA’s measures of education quality across mathematics, science and reading. While we would not
put too much weight in the specific placement / ranking of a country, where countries place across the range is indicative. Over 65 countries
participated in the most recent PISA study in 2012. The PISA surveys are designed in coordination with participating countries and reviewed
